I love GFG! Some of the best tasting food I’ve ever had. From the GFG original to the chocolate bougatsa, you can’t go wrong. My favorite is the chicken gyro. The best in NYC in my opinion.

The spanakopita and Mediterranean pies were stale and hard. A few layers of the dough came off white when biting, so they must've been undercooked. Seriously, the food was so disgusting, I have no idea how this place is in business :/

What a nice eating place! The cafeteria atmosphere was really elegant and beautiful. We sat down the chair and saw the menu but we didn’t know which food was delicious, so we called the waiter and  I could see that he was very helpful. Thank you for your help, guys!  I am writing this review because I want you to be known by many. Keep up the good work!

From food, drinks, wines, salad, and anything else are truly the best here! This cafeteria really has it all and not only their food tastes great, but the prices are not that high too. I really love everything in this place because the foods are all tasty and the staffs are super friendly. A truly wonderful dining experience! Strongly recommended!

Stavros has always been welcoming and remembers my preference for coffee, which is always appreciated. Their coffee and pastries are consistently good, and their location perfect for a pick-me up before heading to work.
Great hospitality and delicious Greek bakery tastes. Their handmade stuffed pies are perfect option for breakfast and brunch. Don't forget to try their deserts also.
I work at NYP/Lower Manhattan Hospital and I’m always looking forward for my espresso. Great staff, friendly and awesome!!!! I highly recommend this place.

I go here many mornings of my week due to it being close to my university campus and I always leave satisfied! I started to go after being recommended their coffee and was very pleasantly surprised by the amazing quality of breakfast and lunch options. The prices are very fair for the quality and I would recommend a visit if you are in the area!

My favorite place for breakfast and lunch in New York! The food is always fresh and so delicious. I stopped going to Starbucks because their coffee is waay better. The staff is warm and very friendly. I always leave with an extra treat. I would give this place 20/10.

I ordered catering from GFG for my son's 100 days party in 2018, the owner and all the staff were very helpful and supportive, because we are vegetarian family, so they offered me a package for 20 people, I didn't even have to think about what to pick! Most important, their food is super delicious! Many of my guess never ate greek food and sweet, and they were all asking where I got these dishes. I will continue ordering from them if I ever have chance to stop by! Highly recommend!!!
One of my fav spots for cafe food. Service is typically great. The bill was decent for the quality.
the sandwich named new yorker is great and delicious. little bit too pricey.

I had try the Hoboken store and I was amazed! Today I was at the city and happy to know they are open again during this situation.. I had a great coffee and the caseri or something pie.. it’s a delicious cheese!!! Staff very friendly and professional like Hoboken!! Highly recommended!!

Been coming here at least 2x a week since it reopened(due to covoid19) nothing bad to say. Everything I've ordered has not disappointed me! They also give samples of their baked goods, fresh from the oven! Definitely recommend to everybody!

I think it kind of conflicts with the professionalism aspect. Other than that, we enjoyed our drinks and coffee cake!

The counter staff with green tint on her hair was extremely rude. She rolled her eyes at us, and when she asked what size of coffee we wanted and we answered 12oz (as stated on the menu board), she became angry and said it’s SMALL. Also, the flat white that we ordered was quite a joke.

She just roll her eyes and told me that she doesn't have any time for me. I make the line as many other customers but still didn't get the service. I was very upset for my first experience in this place. I pay my money to get service. I don't mind if I have to pay extra. If you don't have patience to work with people, just get another job. "I have gone to this bakery 4-5 times and have gotten something new every time. GFG Bakery serves authentic Greek food like spanakopita (several varieties) as well as regular pastries like walnut cake. They also have both traditional Greek frappe and regular coffee. The cheese pie was made with Greek yogurt and was insanely rich practically had to be rolled out of the place. The first time I went, I was brought by a vegan friend. They have a large selection of vegan pastry. The vegan spanakopita is not as good as the regular spanakopita, but I still enjoyed it. The ambiance is clean and fresh, but be warned that there are only about 3 tables and you may have to take your food to go."

GFG Bakery Cafe carries a lot of authentic Greek food. You can find greek cheese pie (tyropita), spinach pie (spanakopita), baklava, kataifi, frappe coffee and many others.  It is very modern inside and has also a seating space. Great for coffee, for a quick meal or snack. The stuff was very polite and helpful. Decent prices.  Worth a visit for sure!
